The Mesen2 adapter's runtime Lua (emucap-core.lua plus the per-system entry
scripts emucap-snes.lua / emucap-sms.lua) is loaded at runtime by Mesen2 (via a
command-line argument); it is not compiled or linked into the Mesen2 binary, so
under the interpreter rule it is not a derivative of Mesen2 (GPL-3.0). It is licensed as the
project default, GPL-2.0-or-later. If a "bindings"-based derivative reading were
adopted, this single adapter would instead be GPL-3.0. See ../../NOTICE.

Full GPL-2.0 text: ../../licenses/GPL-2.0.txt (https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0.txt)
